[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":301},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F":277,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F":286},"\u002FSCSS\u002F20190419\u002F947541843\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":8,"body":9,"category":260,"date":261,"description":262,"extension":263,"lang":264,"meta":265,"navigation":266,"path":267,"readingMinutes":268,"seo":269,"standalone":270,"stem":271,"tags":272,"tldr":274,"updated":274,"url":275,"__hash__":276},"content\u002Fen\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import.md","SCSS Handbook (4) — @import","9475418430","\u002Fscss\u002F20190419\u002F947541843\u002F",{"type":10,"value":11,"toc":253},"minimark",[12,17,26,30,33,36,45,48,55,58,63,73,76,79,84,88,102,108,134,150,157,162,168,173,185,190,198,203,215,220,223,228,235,245,250],[13,14,16],"h2",{"id":15},"intro","Intro",[18,19,20,21,25],"p",{},"SCSS provides ",[22,23,24],"code",{},"@import",", which makes development management way easier when used well.",[13,27,29],{"id":28},"setup","Setup",[18,31,32],{},"The biggest benefit of SCSS is modularization — slicing CSS into chunks so it's easier to maintain. Otherwise updating one thing means scrolling through thousands of lines.",[18,34,35],{},"I'll use VSCode for this walkthrough.",[18,37,38],{},[39,40,44],"a",{"href":41,"rel":42},"https:\u002F\u002Fcode.visualstudio.com\u002F",[43],"nofollow","VSCode",[18,46,47],{},"I'll also install a SASS compile extension for VSCode — Live Sass Compiler:",[18,49,50],{},[51,52],"img",{"alt":53,"src":54},"image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fh58icVs.png",[18,56,57],{},"After installing, you'll see two new buttons in the bottom right of VSCode:",[18,59,60],{},[51,61],{"alt":53,"src":62},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F7oT7wq0.png",[64,65,66,70],"ol",{},[67,68,69],"li",{},"Watch Sass — watches your SASS\u002FSCSS files",[67,71,72],{},"Go Live — starts a local server preview",[18,74,75],{},"This extension watches your SCSS folder and compiles to browser-readable CSS, plus simulates a local server.",[18,77,78],{},"After install, click \"Watch Sass\" in the bottom right before you start writing. When active, it'll look like:",[18,80,81],{},[51,82],{"alt":53,"src":83},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcxLqn7h.png",[13,85,87],{"id":86},"lets-write-some-code","Let's write some code",[18,89,90,91,94,95,98,99],{},"In plain CSS, everything usually ends up in one ",[22,92,93],{},"all.css"," or ",[22,96,97],{},"style.css",", potentially thousands of lines:\n",[51,100],{"alt":53,"src":101},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F5KIyGRq.png",[18,103,104,105,107],{},"Updating one spot becomes painful — your scroll wheel gets a workout. But with SCSS's ",[22,106,24],{},", you can split chunks into their own files, combined with variables, you get a way more maintainable structure (and a saner scroll wheel XD).",[18,109,110,111,114,115,114,118,121,122,124,125,127,128,130,131,133],{},"First, create a few SCSS files: ",[22,112,113],{},"all.scss",", ",[22,116,117],{},"_layout.scss",[22,119,120],{},"_varibale.scss",".\n",[22,123,120],{}," is for custom variables (font sizes, fonts, color palette, etc.)\n",[22,126,117],{}," is the main page layout SCSS\n",[22,129,113],{}," is the entry point that imports everything — mostly just ",[22,132,24],{}," statements",[18,135,136,137,139,140,143,144,146,147,149],{},"Heads up — except for ",[22,138,113],{},", all other files must start with ",[22,141,142],{},"_",". Files starting with ",[22,145,142],{}," are not compiled to CSS individually — only ",[22,148,93],{}," gets generated.",[18,151,152,153,156],{},"ps. Changing the extension to ",[22,154,155],{},".sass"," makes it SASS syntax mode. Worth knowing.",[18,158,159],{},[51,160],{"alt":53,"src":161},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLHg6yNW.png",[18,163,164,165,167],{},"First add variables to ",[22,166,120],{},":",[18,169,170],{},[51,171],{"alt":53,"src":172},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fz1XInGi.png",[18,174,175,176,178,179,181,182,184],{},"Then use ",[22,177,24],{}," in ",[22,180,117],{}," to pull in ",[22,183,120],{}," and use the variables to build a box:",[18,186,187],{},[51,188],{"alt":53,"src":189},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FEvuMh5D.png",[18,191,192,194,195,197],{},[22,193,24],{}," doesn't need the file extension or the ",[22,196,142],{}," prefix.",[18,199,200],{},[51,201],{"alt":53,"src":202},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FvZ6X3IU.png",[18,204,205,206,208,209,211,212,214],{},"Finally, import ",[22,207,117],{}," into ",[22,210,113],{},". You'll notice a new ",[22,213,93],{}," appears in the folder — that's the auto-generated output from the extension.",[18,216,217],{},[51,218],{"alt":53,"src":219},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FHBJ8qG4.png",[18,221,222],{},"You can also open it:",[18,224,225],{},[51,226],{"alt":53,"src":227},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGoYL4t7.png",[18,229,230,231,234],{},"You'll see the content matches what we wrote, but there's an extra line: ",[22,232,233],{},"\u002F* sourceMappingURL=all.css.map *\u002F",".",[18,236,237,238,241,242,167],{},"The map (sourcemap) file helps SCSS developers locate the original SCSS file path — so in the browser dev tools, you'll see the file shown as ",[22,239,240],{},".scss"," instead of ",[22,243,244],{},".css",[18,246,247],{},[51,248],{"alt":53,"src":249},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fdvfb1jv.png",[18,251,252],{},"The benefit: easy to find which SCSS file a specific block came from. Otherwise if you've split things into many files, debugging becomes a nightmare.",{"title":254,"searchDepth":255,"depth":255,"links":256},"",2,[257,258,259],{"id":15,"depth":255,"text":16},{"id":28,"depth":255,"text":29},{"id":86,"depth":255,"text":87},"SCSS","2019-04-19 17:24:30","SCSS provides `@import`, which makes development management way easier when used well.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import","2",{"title":6,"description":262},false,"en\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import",[260,273],"SCSS Handbook",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F","K4LCgTnpb0J_xLrXKcSX0atCIpqDle9pi8s_RF32SjM",{"newer":278,"older":282},{"url":279,"title":280,"date":281},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fjavascript-hoisting-01-explained\u002F","JavaScript Hoisting: Why Does That Variable Say undefined?","2019-04-19 20:33:08",{"url":283,"title":284,"date":285},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-this-keyword-explained\u002F","this Is the Weirdest Thing in JavaScript — Here's How I Finally Got It","2019-04-18 19:46:16",[287,292,296],{"url":288,"title":289,"date":290,"readingMinutes":291},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2025\u002F11\u002F23\u002Fsass-deprecated-import-use-forward-migration\u002F","SCSS Is Deprecating @import?!","2025-11-23 15:32:01","4",{"url":293,"title":294,"date":295,"readingMinutes":268},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F","SCSS Handbook (5) — mixin","2019-04-21 07:24:30",{"url":297,"title":298,"date":299,"readingMinutes":300},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F","SCSS Handbook (3) — Operators","2019-04-18 17:24:30","1",1784087342167]